  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "26. hardened … neck—(De 31:27; Isa 48:4; Ac 7:51).",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "worse than their fathers—(Jer 16:12). In Jer 7:22 He had said, \"your fathers\"; here He says, \"their fathers\"; the change to the third person marks growing alienation from them. He no longer addresses themselves, as it would be a waste of words in the case of such hardened rebels.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
